      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know, i know. \"you matter,\" \"reach out,\" the usual stuff. but it doesnt really change the reality of the day-to-day. it's just words on a screen. it feels like i'm just watching a loop of a life instead of actually living one. if a person is just a collection of data points and unanswered slack messages, what's the point in trying to stay connected when the connection is so hollow? it's like i'm already gone, just waiting for my body to catch up.",
